        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 6:29PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 629 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Glenrio, or 23 miles south of Nara Visa, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Glenrio.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
